cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.MM, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on a content-centric mobile network and device-to-device (D2D) content delivery protocol. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a collaborative filtering (CF)-based approach to learning model parameters. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes several greedy algorithms to solve the cache allocation problems. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper considers file preferences and popularity in a mobile network context. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper considers personalized file preferences and heterogeneity among different users.
